          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "The Shma is one of the prayers one may recite in any language. M. Sotah 7:1\nFor those who choose: The prayer leader at the word Bar'chu (the call to worship) bends\nthe knees and bows from the waist, and at » Adonai stands straight. »77 Baruch Adonai is the\ncommunal response, whereupon the community repeats the choreography of the first line.",
